class Solution {
public:
    int minimumDeleteSum(string s1, string s2) {
        int sum = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < min(s1.length(), s2.length()); i++) {
            if (s1[i] != s2[i]) {
                sum += ASCII_value(s1[i]) - ASCII_value(s2[i]);
            }
        }
        return sum;
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(min(m, n)) where m and n are the lengths of s1 and s2 respectively
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

The solution iterates over the shorter string (min(m, n)) and calculates the difference between the ASCII values of the characters at corresponding positions in s1 and s2. If the characters are different, the sum is updated. This approach ensures that the algorithm only considers the characters that need to be deleted, reducing the time complexity to O(min(m, n)). The space complexity is O(1) since we only use a constant amount of space for the sum variable. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a few operations and does not consume significant energy.

